                <note rend="inline" type="source">817.1051/74</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Secretary of State of a Conversation With
                        the Nicaraguan Chargé</hi> (<hi rend="italic">Tigerino</hi>), <hi
                        rend="italic">May 28, 1925</hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-head" calendar="gregorian"
                        type="conversation-or-meeting-date" when="1925-05-28">May 28, 1925</date>
                </dateline>
                <p>The Chargé stated that Nicaragua had passed the law for the establishment of a
                    constabulary and asked us to give them the names of American officers who would
                    act as instructors. I informed him that we had asked the Navy Department to give
                    us the names of their officers.</p>
            </div>
